#META# documentSubtype: Legal: Sale
#META# writingSupport: paper
#META# writingSupportDetails: Fading/discolouration :: fold lines
#META# writingSupportNotes: flat rotulus carefully folded into a narrow shape, written in discoloured ink that has reddened (with time)
#META# contentSummary: This is one of three Arabic land sale documents from Yarkand which Huart received from Pelliot to study. The original was accompanied by a modern transcription. This is a land sale document dated 489/1096 and concerns the purchase of a vineyard by a certain Fāṭima  for 500 dirhams in the currency of Kāshgar.
#META# dates: The Gregorian calendar: August-September 1096 (1096-08-29 - 1096-09-27)
